WEBVTT

00:01.050 --> 00:03.320
NARRATOR: <i>Previously on</i>
The Handmaid's Tale...

00:03.320 --> 00:05.230
PUTNAM: We lodged
a preliminary complaint

00:05.230 --> 00:07.260
to Canada petitioning
for Nichole's return.

00:07.260 --> 00:08.870
WATERFORD: I thought
this is what you wanted.

00:08.870 --> 00:11.050
Our daughter safe.
In Canada.

00:11.050 --> 00:14.200
We'd like to arrange
a visit with Nichole.

00:14.200 --> 00:16.250
One visit to say goodbye.

00:16.250 --> 00:18.450
Serena Waterford.
Luke Bankole.

00:18.450 --> 00:19.690
What do you want out of this?

00:19.690 --> 00:22.270
I just wanted to see
my daughter.

00:22.270 --> 00:24.180
- She's not your daughter.
SERENA: Or yours.

00:24.180 --> 00:26.220
Do you want to hold her?

00:26.220 --> 00:27.300
[TENSE MUSIC]

00:27.300 --> 00:28.650
Hi, my baby girl.

00:28.650 --> 00:30.820
[NICHOLE COOING]

00:31.560 --> 00:33.020
JUNE: <i>Luke,
there are some things</i>

00:33.020 --> 00:35.040
<i>I need to tell you.</i>

00:35.040 --> 00:36.560
Nichole was born out of love.

00:36.560 --> 00:39.450
<i>Her father's
a driver named Nick.</i>

00:39.450 --> 00:40.900
<i>You met him.</i>

00:40.900 --> 00:42.820
I'm doing what
I need to, to survive.

00:42.820 --> 00:44.630
<i>You should, too.
For Hannah.</i>

00:44.630 --> 00:46.130
<i>This is all for her.</i>

00:46.130 --> 00:48.440
<i>I am trying to get to her.</i>

00:48.440 --> 00:49.640
<i>I promise.</i>

00:49.640 --> 00:51.090
I love you.

00:55.250 --> 00:57.350
WATERFORD: <i>We are a family in mourning.</i>

00:57.350 --> 01:00.180
<i>And we make this request
to the Canadian government.</i>

01:00.180 --> 01:02.130
<i>Our beloved baby daughter,</i>

01:02.130 --> 01:04.290
Nichole Waterford, was kidnapped

01:04.290 --> 01:07.520
by a dangerous fugitive
fleeing our country.

01:07.520 --> 01:09.440
Nichole belongs in Gilead.

01:09.440 --> 01:11.130
We just want her back.

01:19.910 --> 01:21.920
[SOFT PIANO MUSIC]

01:28.540 --> 01:31.170
[PRAYING INDISTINCTLY]

01:31.170 --> 01:33.210
MARTHAS: Blessed and eternal God,

01:33.210 --> 01:35.210
please return
this child of Gilead

01:35.210 --> 01:36.780
to her loving home.

01:36.780 --> 01:38.950
Blessed and eternal God...

01:38.950 --> 01:41.440
JUNE: <i>I see them
every day now.</i>

01:41.440 --> 01:44.190
<i>They've heard
the Waterfords' plea.</i>

01:44.190 --> 01:46.410
<i>They're praying for Nichole.</i>

01:46.410 --> 01:47.410
[PRAYING INDISTINCTLY]

01:47.410 --> 01:49.780
<i>"Blessed and eternal God,
please return</i>

01:49.780 --> 01:52.790
<i>this child of Gilead
to her loving home."</i>

01:54.030 --> 01:57.260
<i>And this is all I know
about my baby.</i>

01:57.260 --> 02:00.440
<i>If they're praying,
then she's still safe.</i>

02:00.440 --> 02:03.030
<i>If they're praying, she is
still beyond their reach.</i>

02:03.030 --> 02:05.060
<i>Even if just.</i>

02:06.680 --> 02:08.979
<i>I have my own prayers.</i>

02:08.979 --> 02:11.580
<i>I pray that their prayers
go unanswered.</i>

02:13.030 --> 02:15.440
<i>And I pray for Serena.</i>

02:15.440 --> 02:17.470
<i>May she find her way back,</i>

02:17.470 --> 02:19.090
<i>may she see past
her broken heart</i>

02:19.090 --> 02:20.800
<i>and remember that
Nichole is better off</i>

02:20.800 --> 02:22.260
<i>where she is.</i>

02:22.260 --> 02:25.010
<i>May she convince Fred
to let things lie.</i>

02:25.890 --> 02:27.820
<i>Or may they both get hit
by a fucking truck.</i>

02:27.820 --> 02:29.360
[AMPLIFIED CAR NOISE]

02:31.880 --> 02:33.860
<i>I'm honestly down for either.</i>

