02:43.480 --> 02:45.490
LAWRENCE: Can't a Martha do that?

02:46.920 --> 02:49.250
Just making myself useful, sir.

02:51.920 --> 02:53.580
Right.

02:54.820 --> 02:56.840
You should go pack.

02:57.890 --> 02:59.480
Waterford asked to borrow you.

02:59.480 --> 03:01.880
He's trying to force
the Canadians to the table.

03:01.880 --> 03:04.520
Talk about repatriating
his daughter.

03:04.520 --> 03:06.230
OFJOSEPH: Don't call her that.

03:07.240 --> 03:09.690
Please, don't call her that.

03:14.250 --> 03:16.240
LAWRENCE: He set up a...

03:16.240 --> 03:19.030
week of public prayer in D. C.

03:19.030 --> 03:22.670
It's a good idea, actually.

03:22.670 --> 03:25.240
Canadians'll feel the pressure.

03:25.240 --> 03:27.460
He wants the whole household.

03:27.460 --> 03:29.460
Better visual.

03:31.870 --> 03:33.900
Mrs. Waterford will be there?

03:33.900 --> 03:35.920
Whither thou goest.

03:35.920 --> 03:37.370
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

03:37.370 --> 03:38.740
Train's at 4:00.

03:51.660 --> 03:54.700
[TRAIN HORN BLARES]

04:09.250 --> 04:11.770
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

04:11.770 --> 04:13.790
[MUMBLES]

04:23.240 --> 04:24.810
P.A.: <i>National Station.</i>

04:24.810 --> 04:26.820
<i>National Station, next.</i>

04:26.820 --> 04:28.600
[TRAIN BELL RINGING]

04:30.350 --> 04:33.270
[TRAIN HORN BLARES]

04:33.270 --> 04:34.570
[SINISTER MUSIC]

04:47.660 --> 04:49.660
P.A.: <i>Track change announcement...</i>

04:52.440 --> 04:53.670
AUNT LYDIA: Ah!

04:53.670 --> 04:56.030
Isn't this magnificent?

04:56.030 --> 04:58.830
The old one was so beautiful.

04:58.830 --> 05:00.790
It was designed by a heretic.

05:00.790 --> 05:04.010
Destroyed for
the glory of Gilead.

05:04.010 --> 05:06.050
Ah, I'm pumped.

05:06.050 --> 05:07.050
[LAUGHS]

05:07.050 --> 05:08.500
Didn't they used to say?

05:08.500 --> 05:10.130
Are you pumped, dear?

05:10.130 --> 05:11.240
Oh, yeah, I'm pumped,

05:11.240 --> 05:12.670
Aunt Lydia.

05:12.670 --> 05:15.110
No one likes a sourpuss, Ofjoseph.

05:18.030 --> 05:19.890
Wonderful!

05:19.890 --> 05:21.740
The devotion!

05:37.050 --> 05:38.920
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

05:38.920 --> 05:40.290
All right, dear,

05:40.290 --> 05:41.660
see you tomorrow.

05:41.660 --> 05:43.450
Go to your spot.

05:43.450 --> 05:45.460
My spot?

05:45.460 --> 05:47.050
They don't stand for disorder,

05:47.050 --> 05:48.870
not in the capital.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.050
Go on, now.

05:50.050 --> 05:51.600
You be a good girl.

05:51.600 --> 05:53.970
[ALARM BUZZING]

06:02.860 --> 06:04.490
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

06:04.490 --> 06:06.560
[TENSE MUSIC]

06:11.250 --> 06:12.420
[P.A. SYSTEM CHIMES]

06:12.420 --> 06:13.860
P.A.: <i>For your own safety</i>

06:13.860 --> 06:15.680
<i>and the safety
of those you love,</i>

06:15.680 --> 06:17.890
<i>please stand back
from the platform edge.</i>

06:17.890 --> 06:19.470
<i>Remember to mind the gap</i>

06:19.470 --> 06:21.700
<i>between the train
and the platform.</i>

06:21.700 --> 06:23.720
<i>Have a blessed evening.</i>

06:30.290 --> 06:32.320
Blessed be the fruit.

06:34.650 --> 06:36.730
May the Lord open.

06:38.450 --> 06:41.020
Welcome to Washington.

06:49.880 --> 06:51.050
Blessed are the silent,

06:51.050 --> 06:52.900
for only they will hear
the voice of the Lord.

06:52.900 --> 06:54.760
Head down, please.

07:00.400 --> 07:01.790
WATERFORD: There you are!

07:08.880 --> 07:10.650
AUNT: Blessed evening, Commander.

07:10.650 --> 07:12.980
WATERFORD: She's ours. Waterford.

07:12.980 --> 07:15.000
AUNT: Yes.
Of course, sir.

07:15.000 --> 07:17.570
We're guests of
High Commander Winslow.

07:17.570 --> 07:19.440
Praise be.

07:20.890 --> 07:22.740
Up you go.

07:25.770 --> 07:27.670
All together again.

07:27.670 --> 07:29.140
Isn't this nice?

07:29.140 --> 07:31.470
Yes, sir.

07:31.470 --> 07:34.040
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

07:34.040 --> 07:35.990
Under His eye,
Mrs. Waterford.

07:35.990 --> 07:38.030
I hope you're well.

07:41.030 --> 07:43.480
[ALARM BUZZING]

07:43.480 --> 07:44.660
And we're off,

07:44.660 --> 07:47.100
like a herd of dusty turtles.

07:49.230 --> 07:50.620
[P.A. SYSTEM CHIMES]

07:50.620 --> 07:53.560
P.A.: <i>This is a pre-boarding
announcement for Columbia.</i>

07:53.560 --> 07:55.660
<i>Please make your way
to Platform 5.</i>

07:55.660 --> 07:57.670
<i>Columbia on Platform 5.</i>

07:57.670 --> 07:59.710
May the Lord open.

08:01.030 --> 08:02.040
Hey.

08:02.040 --> 08:03.240
Hi.

08:04.240 --> 08:05.460
I miss you.

08:05.460 --> 08:06.900
You, too.

08:06.900 --> 08:09.350
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

08:19.920 --> 08:21.960
[WHISPERS]
She can't want this.

08:23.650 --> 08:25.470
She misses the baby.

08:25.470 --> 08:27.110
We all do.

08:29.430 --> 08:31.880
It's the only thing
she ever wanted.

08:36.860 --> 08:38.929
[TURNSTILE SQUEAKS]

08:38.929 --> 08:40.970
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

08:46.100 --> 08:48.380
[SIRENS BLARING]

08:49.410 --> 08:52.010
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

08:56.720 --> 08:59.270
[TIRES SQUEALING]

08:59.270 --> 09:00.300
[DOGS BARK]

09:00.300 --> 09:01.930
[DOOR CLOSES]

09:04.630 --> 09:05.630
[DOGS BARK]

09:05.630 --> 09:06.870
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

09:07.780 --> 09:10.400
WATERFORD: Isn't this beautiful?

09:10.400 --> 09:13.460
SERENA: We should've
stayed in a hotel.

09:13.460 --> 09:15.470
WATERFORD: No need
to be nervous.

09:15.470 --> 09:16.810
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

09:18.670 --> 09:20.790
WATERFORD: I've heard
they're very down-to-earth.

09:22.450 --> 09:24.480
This is an opportunity.

09:27.220 --> 09:29.440
For <i>whom</i> ?

09:29.440 --> 09:30.450
WATERFORD: Us.

09:31.860 --> 09:33.820
All of us.

09:33.820 --> 09:35.220
Nichole.

09:35.220 --> 09:36.790
[DOOR OPENS]

09:38.140 --> 09:40.160
WATERFORD: Blessed evening.

09:49.680 --> 09:51.700
[DOOR CLOSES]
[BIRDS CHIRP]

10:07.960 --> 10:10.350
WINSLOW: I'm so sorry.

10:10.350 --> 10:12.670
Conference calls.

10:12.670 --> 10:15.470
Welcome.

10:15.470 --> 10:16.800
Blessed evening.

10:16.800 --> 10:18.830
It's an honor, Commander.

10:20.450 --> 10:22.200
Waterford.

10:22.200 --> 10:23.240
SERENA: Thank you

10:23.240 --> 10:24.970
for inviting us to your blessed home.

10:24.970 --> 10:26.130
WINSLOW: You can thank Mrs. Winslow

10:26.130 --> 10:27.550
for the invitation.

10:28.610 --> 10:30.250
I will be sure to.

10:30.250 --> 10:31.660
Thank you.

10:31.660 --> 10:33.530
Please.

10:35.230 --> 10:37.750
Well.
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:37.750 --> 10:40.170
We have an exciting
week planned.

10:40.170 --> 10:41.830
Yes.

10:43.360 --> 10:46.060
We have to be judicious

10:46.060 --> 10:49.050
about the images
we release to the world.

10:49.050 --> 10:50.310
WATERFORD: Absolutely.

10:50.310 --> 10:52.350
The correct image can sway opinion.

10:53.890 --> 10:55.450
[BIRD CHIRPS]

10:55.450 --> 10:56.480
[RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]

10:56.480 --> 10:57.870
[DOOR OPENS]

10:57.870 --> 10:59.500
Good night, Daddy!

10:59.500 --> 11:00.990
Good night, my love!

11:00.990 --> 11:02.930
[KISSING]
[CURIOUS MUSIC]

11:02.930 --> 11:04.650
This is Polly,

11:04.650 --> 11:06.410
who obviously has
forgotten how to knock.

11:06.410 --> 11:08.960
WATERFORD: [CHUCKLES] Blessed evening,
Polly.

11:08.960 --> 11:10.820
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

11:10.820 --> 11:12.990
WINSLOW: Oh-oh, oh!

11:12.990 --> 11:15.240
[CHILDREN LAUGHING AND EXCLAIMING]

11:15.240 --> 11:16.780
Where are my boys?
Okay.

11:16.780 --> 11:20.600
[WINSLOW PLAY FIGHTING]

11:20.600 --> 11:21.620
MRS. WINSLOW: Micah!

11:21.620 --> 11:22.630
WINSLOW: There's my boys. Okay!

11:22.630 --> 11:25.690
Jeez! Everyone else
is ready for bed.

11:25.690 --> 11:26.990
Hi.

11:26.990 --> 11:28.020
Hi!

11:28.020 --> 11:29.880
[BABY FUSSING]

11:29.880 --> 11:31.450
Welcome.
I'm Olivia.

11:31.450 --> 11:32.960
It's just lovely to meet you.

11:32.960 --> 11:33.980
WATERFORD: A pleasure.

11:33.980 --> 11:35.430
Thank you for inviting us

11:35.430 --> 11:36.680
to your blessed home.

11:36.680 --> 11:38.550
Please forgive our chaos.

11:38.550 --> 11:41.000
Introduce yourselves
to Mr. and Mrs. Waterford.

11:42.050 --> 11:43.400
This is Isaiah.

11:43.400 --> 11:45.490
He's the easy one,
if you can believe it.

11:45.490 --> 11:46.980
SERENA: Oh. Hello.

11:46.980 --> 11:48.860
Uh, I'm Serena Joy.

11:48.860 --> 11:50.380
It's a pleasure
to meet all of you.

11:50.380 --> 11:51.410
How do you do.

11:51.410 --> 11:52.580
Fred Waterford.
Hi.

11:52.580 --> 11:54.260
WATERFORD: How do you, sir?
SADIE: I'm Sadie.

11:54.260 --> 11:56.120
[WHISPERS] Are they all yours?

11:56.120 --> 11:57.970
Who else's would
they be? Micah!

11:57.970 --> 12:00.160
[INDISTINCT PLAYFUL CHATTER]

12:05.240 --> 12:06.700
[BABY COOS]

12:06.700 --> 12:08.240
MRS. WINSLOW: Tamara,

12:08.240 --> 12:09.930
can you get them settled, please?

12:09.930 --> 12:11.250
[WINSLOW CLEARS THROAT]

12:11.250 --> 12:12.520
MRS. WINSLOW: Okay.
Let's get dinner.

12:12.520 --> 12:14.530
[INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES]

12:23.580 --> 12:25.600
[GHOULISH MUSIC]

12:48.820 --> 12:51.190
RITA: Have you ever seen
that many before?

12:51.190 --> 12:53.460
OFJOSEPH: No.

12:53.460 --> 12:55.660
RITA: The most I've ever
seen in one house was...

12:55.660 --> 12:57.880
three.

12:57.880 --> 12:59.900
They had, like, <i>five.</i>

13:06.440 --> 13:08.240
MARTHA: You'll be staying here,

13:08.240 --> 13:10.570
with Ofgeorge.

13:10.570 --> 13:11.650
Praise be.

13:11.650 --> 13:13.680
Thank you.

13:17.050 --> 13:18.450
[RETREATING FOOTSTEPS]
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:18.450 --> 13:20.420
They have a Handmaid?

13:20.420 --> 13:22.250
Privileges of rank,

13:22.250 --> 13:24.870
I guess.

13:24.870 --> 13:27.050
Blessed night.

13:27.050 --> 13:29.790
[RETREATING FOOTSTEPS]

13:29.790 --> 13:30.790
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:30.790 --> 13:33.420
[GRANDFATHER CLOCK RINGS CREEPILY]

13:44.410 --> 13:45.880
[KNOCKING]

13:45.880 --> 13:46.960
Yes?

13:46.960 --> 13:48.000
[DOOR OPENS]

13:50.880 --> 13:52.520
Settling in?

13:52.520 --> 13:53.950
Yes.

13:53.950 --> 13:55.890
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:55.890 --> 13:58.250
Thank you for checking in.

14:00.690 --> 14:01.750
All those children.

14:01.750 --> 14:03.400
It's remarkable.

14:03.400 --> 14:06.270
It's a miracle.

14:06.270 --> 14:08.410
A miracle.

14:08.410 --> 14:11.890
Someday it won't be so unusual,

14:11.890 --> 14:14.380
by His grace.

14:14.380 --> 14:15.650
[INHALES]

14:15.650 --> 14:16.650
Is there any news

14:16.650 --> 14:18.340
from Commander Winslow
about tomorrow?

14:19.650 --> 14:21.870
Oh, still nothing from the Canadians.

14:21.870 --> 14:23.450
They...

14:23.450 --> 14:26.890
could ask a neutral party to intervene.

14:26.890 --> 14:28.030
SERENA: They could.

14:28.030 --> 14:30.250
I pray.

14:30.250 --> 14:31.680
Our turnaround will be fast.

14:31.680 --> 14:33.260
Film in the morning,

14:33.260 --> 14:35.890
get images on
Canadian news by night.

14:35.890 --> 14:37.670
Bottom line, the more...

14:37.670 --> 14:38.880
media we generate,

14:38.880 --> 14:40.910
the more pressure they'll feel.

14:42.890 --> 14:45.040
Trust me.

14:45.040 --> 14:47.250
<i>This</i>,

14:47.250 --> 14:48.660
I know about.

14:52.010 --> 14:55.260
I should probably get some rest.

14:55.260 --> 14:56.540
WATERFORD: Of course.

14:56.540 --> 14:58.550
I still have work to do.

15:02.350 --> 15:03.520
Here.

15:08.240 --> 15:10.060
Just so everything looks...

15:10.060 --> 15:11.480
right.

15:14.630 --> 15:16.050
[DOOR OPENS]

15:16.050 --> 15:17.240
Good night, Fred.

15:20.020 --> 15:23.440
[DARK PIANO MUSIC]

16:05.040 --> 16:07.000
[CAR DRIVES BY]

16:07.000 --> 16:08.040
[DOOR OPENS]

16:08.040 --> 16:09.900
[DOOR CREAKS]

16:09.900 --> 16:10.920
[DOGS BARK IN DISTANCE]

16:10.920 --> 16:12.580
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS]

16:14.890 --> 16:16.550
Hey.

16:18.790 --> 16:20.720
Blessed be the fruit.

16:27.860 --> 16:29.900
I'm Ofjoseph.

16:37.450 --> 16:39.890
I'm sorry to invade
your space like this.

16:39.890 --> 16:40.910
[HELICOPTER FLYING BY]

16:46.250 --> 16:48.280
Pray, forgive me.

16:50.450 --> 16:53.060
So, you must be...

16:53.060 --> 16:55.160
Ofgeorge?

16:55.160 --> 16:57.170
[FRIGHTENING MUSIC]

17:05.440 --> 17:07.079
Sorry.

17:10.230 --> 17:11.869
Nice to meet you.

17:17.670 --> 17:19.670
[UNZIPS BOOTS]

17:26.030 --> 17:28.040
[BOOTS THUD]

17:32.910 --> 17:34.930
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

17:37.640 --> 17:38.910
[DOOR OPENS]

17:38.910 --> 17:40.440
[APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS]

17:40.440 --> 17:41.880
WATERFORD: Is this all we have?

17:41.880 --> 17:43.350
AUNT LYDIA: I believe
so, Commander.

17:43.350 --> 17:45.240
They do have duties
of their own.

17:45.240 --> 17:47.240
WATERFORD: What about their
duties to their country?

17:47.240 --> 17:48.980
All right. Bring 'em over here.

17:48.980 --> 17:50.240
AUNT LYDIA: Go on now, girls.

17:50.240 --> 17:51.460
That's it.
[DOOR CLOSES]

17:51.460 --> 17:53.460
WATERFORD: Semi-circle.

17:53.460 --> 17:55.830
Facing the wings.

17:57.660 --> 17:59.070
Good.

18:04.680 --> 18:06.880
Ofjoseph?
You'll...

18:06.880 --> 18:09.420
stand in the middle,

18:09.420 --> 18:11.210
between Mrs. Waterford

18:11.210 --> 18:13.260
and myself.

18:13.260 --> 18:15.740
Come up.

18:15.740 --> 18:17.270
Come, come.

18:25.870 --> 18:28.010
Thank you.

18:29.470 --> 18:30.650
Handmaids...

18:30.650 --> 18:31.660
[WHISPERS] Serena.

18:31.660 --> 18:33.050
WATERFORD: The cameras
can be distracting.

18:33.050 --> 18:34.460
Try and forget they're there.

18:34.460 --> 18:37.030
How many more of these
videos is he gonna do?

18:37.030 --> 18:38.670
WATERFORD: And remember to be at peace.

18:38.670 --> 18:40.270
- As many as it takes.
WATERFORD: Okay.

18:40.270 --> 18:41.380
Everyone ready?
[DOOR OPENS]

18:41.380 --> 18:43.710
Now, Ofjoseph, <i>I'll</i> start.

18:43.710 --> 18:45.400
They'll follow
<i>your</i> lead to pray.

18:45.400 --> 18:46.420
Understand?

18:47.580 --> 18:49.150
[DOOR CLOSES]
This is going to be

18:49.150 --> 18:51.020
sweeping and stately.

18:52.540 --> 18:54.970
I want a real feeling
of grandeur.

18:56.800 --> 18:58.510
Looks beautiful, sir.

18:58.510 --> 19:00.210
Well, hello,

19:00.210 --> 19:02.050
Commander.

19:02.050 --> 19:03.960
[TENSE MUSIC]

19:03.960 --> 19:05.990
What a nice surprise.

19:07.240 --> 19:08.650
I uh, I called on the Winslows,

19:08.650 --> 19:10.470
they sent me over.

19:10.470 --> 19:11.890
WATERFORD: Really?

19:11.890 --> 19:13.260
I thought you were on your way

19:13.260 --> 19:14.840
to the Front?

19:14.840 --> 19:16.810
I should be getting
my orders any day.

19:19.680 --> 19:20.940
WATERFORD: Would you mind

19:20.940 --> 19:23.220
standing in for me?

19:23.220 --> 19:25.310
Just for this shot.

19:37.600 --> 19:38.890
Nice girl like you

19:38.890 --> 19:40.720
in a place like this.

19:45.830 --> 19:49.360
WATERFORD: Good, good.

19:52.010 --> 19:54.380
Thank you...

19:54.380 --> 19:55.380
son.

20:03.620 --> 20:05.890
[WATERFORD CLEARS THROAT]

20:05.890 --> 20:07.030
Ready?

20:11.490 --> 20:12.690
Action.

20:12.690 --> 20:14.210
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:14.210 --> 20:16.000
[CAMERA BEEPS]

20:16.000 --> 20:19.450
He who is merciful,

20:19.450 --> 20:21.460
hear our prayer.

20:46.240 --> 20:48.000
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

20:48.000 --> 20:50.030
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

20:50.030 --> 20:53.030
["TWINKLE, TWINKLE, LITTLE STAR"
PLAYS SOFTLY IN BACKGROUND]

21:00.220 --> 21:02.220
[TOYS SQUEAK]

21:02.220 --> 21:03.350
Cheers to the queens.

21:03.350 --> 21:04.870
BOTH: And cheers to the prince.

21:04.870 --> 21:07.020
RITA: Yes, yes, and he
can have some more.

21:07.020 --> 21:08.390
And scoop this around.

21:08.390 --> 21:10.400
But the secret is,
you go very fast.

21:10.400 --> 21:12.540
[RITA CONTINUES IN BACKGROUND]

21:24.460 --> 21:26.160
Good morning,
Mrs. Waterford.

21:27.460 --> 21:28.470
Good morning.

21:28.470 --> 21:31.330
ISAIAH: Yum,
yum, yum, yum.

21:31.330 --> 21:33.460
[CHILDREN BABBLE IN BACKGROUND]

21:33.460 --> 21:35.490
[WHISPERS] Serena.

21:39.150 --> 21:41.320
I know you don't want this.

21:49.290 --> 21:51.320
Please talk to me.

21:59.250 --> 22:01.250
We can talk if you like.

22:04.440 --> 22:06.250
But you have to understand that

22:06.250 --> 22:09.130
seeing her changed
everything for me.

22:13.040 --> 22:14.680
I know.

22:21.240 --> 22:23.260
Then what is there
to talk about?

22:25.460 --> 22:27.650
Because seeing her changed...

22:27.650 --> 22:29.300
you.

22:29.300 --> 22:32.030
[SOMBER MUSIC]

22:32.030 --> 22:33.240
It changed you,

22:33.240 --> 22:34.580
it didn't change...

22:34.580 --> 22:35.590
this...

22:35.590 --> 22:36.610
place.

22:40.880 --> 22:43.660
She deserves...

22:43.660 --> 22:45.520
better.

22:48.680 --> 22:50.900
Our girl deserves better.

22:53.490 --> 22:55.430
And I <i>know</i>

22:55.430 --> 22:57.440
that you know that.

23:07.030 --> 23:09.030
They seem happy here.

23:11.450 --> 23:13.330
Have you seen their Handmaid?

23:15.080 --> 23:16.730
WATERFORD: Rita.

23:16.730 --> 23:18.230
Rita, can you steam this...

23:18.230 --> 23:19.830
RITA: Yes, yes, of course.

23:19.830 --> 23:20.850
...for me, please?

23:20.850 --> 23:22.240
RITA: Commander Waterford.

23:22.240 --> 23:23.240
Thank you.

23:23.240 --> 23:25.130
We've got movement.

23:25.130 --> 23:26.850
Canadians have asked the Swiss

23:26.850 --> 23:28.950
to conduct interviews.

23:31.640 --> 23:33.650
They'll act as a neutral party.

23:33.650 --> 23:35.870
What does this mean for Nichole?

23:35.870 --> 23:38.650
It's a small step,

23:38.650 --> 23:40.020
but it's a step.

23:41.030 --> 23:42.250
They've asked to speak

23:42.250 --> 23:44.130
with the whole household.

23:45.030 --> 23:46.940
Together.

23:54.250 --> 23:56.270
OFJOSEPH: Please.

24:03.660 --> 24:05.680
WATERFORD: Put on a clean dress.

24:07.450 --> 24:09.460
We all want to make
a good impression.

24:14.670 --> 24:16.680
[DRAMATIC VIOLIN MUSIC]

24:20.510 --> 24:21.510
[HORN HONKS]

24:31.580 --> 24:33.580
[DOORS CLOSE]

24:55.200 --> 24:56.640
[DOOR OPENS]

24:56.640 --> 24:59.030
MATTIAS: Thank you,
Mr. and Mrs. Waterford.

24:59.030 --> 25:01.020
That was illuminating.
[DOOR CLOSES]

25:01.020 --> 25:02.600
WATERFORD: Thank you
for helping us rectify

25:02.600 --> 25:04.650
this tragic injustice.

25:04.650 --> 25:06.500
MATTIAS: Yes.

25:08.620 --> 25:12.030
Next,
we will speak with Ofjoseph.

25:12.030 --> 25:13.990
WATERFORD: Of course. Ofjoseph!

25:13.990 --> 25:15.030
MATTIAS: Thank you, Commander.

25:15.030 --> 25:17.050
We'd like to speak
with her alone.

25:20.030 --> 25:21.870
Well, she's here as a...

25:21.870 --> 25:23.040
member of...

25:23.040 --> 25:24.850
my household.
In our culture,

25:24.850 --> 25:25.860
[CHUCKLES]

25:25.860 --> 25:28.250
it wouldn't be appropriate.

25:28.250 --> 25:29.480
MATTIAS: Yes.

25:29.480 --> 25:32.870
But we would like
to speak with her alone.

25:32.870 --> 25:35.310
As long as Ofjoseph
has no objection.

25:39.450 --> 25:41.240
None at all.

25:42.270 --> 25:44.100
MATTIAS: Good.

25:57.440 --> 25:59.710
[WHISPERS] Don't be stupid.

26:00.880 --> 26:02.910
MATTIAS: If you please.

26:26.670 --> 26:28.230
[RETREATING FOOTSTEPS]

26:28.230 --> 26:29.450
[PEN CLICKS]

26:29.450 --> 26:31.590
[PEN SCRATCHING ON PAPER]

26:43.450 --> 26:45.480
Ofjoseph, is that right?

26:49.650 --> 26:52.260
Do you prefer Ms. Osborn?

26:52.260 --> 26:54.520
June is fine.

26:54.520 --> 26:56.420
Send them out.

26:57.430 --> 26:59.450
You can be candid in this room,

26:59.450 --> 27:00.740
Ms. Osborn.

27:01.470 --> 27:03.470
If you want me to talk to you,

27:03.470 --> 27:05.580
then send them out.

27:10.870 --> 27:12.220
[DOOR OPENS, BEEPS]

27:14.020 --> 27:15.120
[DOOR CLOSES, BEEPS]

27:15.120 --> 27:17.090
What would you like us to know?

27:18.250 --> 27:20.470
I am the child's mother.

27:22.090 --> 27:25.010
And I want Nichole to stay in Canada.

27:26.230 --> 27:27.660
I see.

27:27.660 --> 27:28.680
OFJOSEPH: I do not expect you

27:28.680 --> 27:30.700
to feel sorry for me

27:30.700 --> 27:32.040
or to...

27:32.040 --> 27:34.490
promise that you're going
to change things.

27:37.650 --> 27:39.910
I just need to keep Nichole there.

27:40.650 --> 27:43.870
We understand your feelings.

27:43.870 --> 27:46.300
The situation is complicated.

27:49.280 --> 27:51.660
Commander Waterford
is not her father.

27:52.660 --> 27:53.870
SOFIA: We do know that,

27:53.870 --> 27:56.490
from our associates in Canada.

27:56.490 --> 27:58.300
There was an audio cassette.

28:02.880 --> 28:05.240
[VIOLIN MUSIC]

28:05.240 --> 28:07.860
So she can stay there, then.

28:07.860 --> 28:10.670
If that's what both
her parents want.

28:10.670 --> 28:12.090
MATTIAS: Gilead is ah...

28:12.090 --> 28:14.430
an extremely powerful country...

28:14.430 --> 28:16.270
militarily.

28:16.270 --> 28:19.770
Canada is eager
to avoid conflict.

28:20.870 --> 28:22.240
What do you need
from me in order

28:22.240 --> 28:24.100
to keep her there?

28:25.990 --> 28:27.470
LENA: Our biggest gap

28:27.470 --> 28:28.650
is information.

28:28.650 --> 28:29.660
SOFIA: Gilead has been

28:29.660 --> 28:31.260
a black box for years.

28:31.260 --> 28:32.680
We don't know
how decisions are made,

28:32.680 --> 28:34.530
where the power lies.

28:34.530 --> 28:37.460
The more we know,

28:37.460 --> 28:39.070
the more we can do.

28:39.070 --> 28:41.670
What if I brought you
someone who would talk?

28:41.670 --> 28:44.030
A Commander.

28:44.030 --> 28:45.720
An Eye.

28:45.720 --> 28:48.390
It seems unlikely that
kind of person would...

28:48.390 --> 28:49.400
be cooperative.

28:49.400 --> 28:51.240
I'll persuade him.

28:51.240 --> 28:52.680
[TENSE MUSIC]

28:52.680 --> 28:54.230
LENA: From the cassette.

28:54.230 --> 28:55.950
The father of the child.

28:55.950 --> 28:58.400
SOFIA: Are you two
still in a relationship?

29:00.260 --> 29:02.020
It's...

29:02.020 --> 29:04.560
It's complicated.

29:04.560 --> 29:06.590
MATTIAS: If Commander Blaine
would talk to us,

29:06.590 --> 29:10.650
it could be of
enormous consequence.

29:10.650 --> 29:13.900
It could help us to protect Nichole.

29:13.900 --> 29:16.040
That would be the trade, then?

29:16.040 --> 29:18.810
SOFIA: I don't know that
we can promise explicitly.

29:18.810 --> 29:21.070
I need it to be explicit.

29:29.080 --> 29:31.240
Bring us Commander Blaine,

29:31.240 --> 29:33.250
and we have a deal.

29:54.680 --> 29:56.050
[DOOR OPENS, BEEPS]

29:56.050 --> 29:58.050
[INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO]

30:00.470 --> 30:02.470
["EVERYDAY" BY BUDDY HOLLY]

30:02.470 --> 30:04.030
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:04.030 --> 30:07.670
<i>♪ Everyday
it's a-getting closer ♪</i>

30:07.670 --> 30:11.250
<i>♪ Going faster
than a rollercoaster ♪</i>

30:11.250 --> 30:16.040
<i>♪ Love like yours will
surely come my way ♪</i>

30:16.040 --> 30:18.270
<i>♪ A-hey,
a-hey-hey ♪</i>

30:18.270 --> 30:20.230
[SONG CONTINUES ON RADIO]

30:21.100 --> 30:23.740
You brought the Swiss
to the table.

30:23.740 --> 30:24.770
Power of prayer.

30:24.770 --> 30:25.860
No.

30:25.860 --> 30:27.950
The presentation of that power.

30:31.020 --> 30:33.240
A stroke of genius.

30:33.240 --> 30:34.880
Very kind.

30:36.450 --> 30:38.470
WINSLOW: You know,

30:40.650 --> 30:42.660
I underestimated you,
though, Waterford.

30:42.660 --> 30:44.690
I'd heard about your recent...

30:46.760 --> 30:48.780
difficulties, and...

30:50.060 --> 30:52.080
Well, I made assumptions.

30:53.940 --> 30:55.570
Stand up.

30:58.110 --> 31:00.150
Here's to your bright future.

31:01.310 --> 31:03.330
Perhaps here in D. C.

31:03.330 --> 31:05.650
[MUSIC BOX LULLABY]

31:05.650 --> 31:06.870
A posting in D. C.

31:06.870 --> 31:08.220
Would be an honor, sir.

31:13.390 --> 31:15.720
George, please.

31:15.720 --> 31:17.360
[CHUCKLES]

31:20.500 --> 31:21.990
[EXHALES]

31:23.030 --> 31:25.450
We'll just let this...

31:25.450 --> 31:27.460
ordeal play out.

31:30.890 --> 31:32.910
But a man of your talents...

31:36.340 --> 31:38.350
could be an asset.

31:38.350 --> 31:39.450
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

31:39.450 --> 31:40.880
POLLY: Daddy?
WINSLOW: Yes, love.

31:40.880 --> 31:42.190
POLLY: Would you and Mr. Waterford

31:42.190 --> 31:43.350
have a tea party with me?

31:43.350 --> 31:44.440
I can think of nothing

31:44.440 --> 31:46.050
I'd rather do.
Fred?

31:47.090 --> 31:48.890
You'll never taste
a better cup of tea.

31:48.890 --> 31:49.910
[CHUCKLES]

31:51.450 --> 31:52.830
Oh!

31:52.830 --> 31:54.700
Then I...

31:54.700 --> 31:57.650
happily accept your...

31:57.650 --> 31:58.880
kind invitation.

31:58.880 --> 32:01.020
POLLY: Yay!

32:01.020 --> 32:02.160
[POLLY LAUGHING]

32:22.230 --> 32:24.250
WATERFORD: Let the tea party begin.

32:24.250 --> 32:26.040
WINSLOW: We have to take care of you...

32:26.040 --> 32:28.410
Your lions, I mean...

32:28.410 --> 32:31.370
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

32:31.370 --> 32:32.630
[LAUGHTER]

32:32.630 --> 32:35.570
MRS. WINSLOW: Oversized children,
aren't they?

32:35.570 --> 32:36.580
Men.

32:36.580 --> 32:38.590
Yes, Fred can be a bit much.

32:40.440 --> 32:41.860
Whenever he gets a new idea,

32:41.860 --> 32:43.250
he gets very excited.

32:43.250 --> 32:44.590
George is the same

32:44.590 --> 32:46.050
when he finds a new friend.

32:46.050 --> 32:47.250
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

32:47.250 --> 32:49.870
I know this is a bit taboo,

32:49.870 --> 32:52.020
but I loved your book.

32:55.240 --> 32:57.880
Thank you.

32:57.880 --> 33:00.230
It's very kind of you to say.

33:00.230 --> 33:01.870
MRS. WINSLOW: You...
You really...

33:01.870 --> 33:03.640
just saved me.

33:03.640 --> 33:05.670
You should have seen us before.

33:05.670 --> 33:07.840
Me at one corporate law firm,

33:07.840 --> 33:09.600
George at another.

33:09.600 --> 33:12.060
No time for a family.

33:12.060 --> 33:14.600
You have a beautiful family now.

33:14.600 --> 33:16.580
You will too.

33:16.580 --> 33:18.470
WATERFORD: I think
there's something missing

33:18.470 --> 33:20.490
from the tea.

33:20.490 --> 33:22.660
Sorry to intrude.
Uh...

33:22.660 --> 33:25.100
May we borrow some sugar?

33:26.030 --> 33:27.440
[SWEET PIANO MUSIC]

33:27.440 --> 33:28.780
[LAUGHS]

33:28.780 --> 33:31.430
[IMITATES ROARING]

33:31.430 --> 33:33.870
[LAUGHS]

33:33.870 --> 33:35.500
Of course.

33:44.880 --> 33:46.040
POLLY: Hey,
that's mine!

33:46.040 --> 33:47.680
MRS. WINSLOW: Oh!

33:52.440 --> 33:54.080
Lost my lion.

33:54.080 --> 33:55.600
[MRS. WINSLOW CHUCKLES]

33:57.040 --> 33:58.250
WATERFORD: Got sugar.

33:58.250 --> 33:59.680
Okay.

34:02.580 --> 34:04.590
[WIND HOWLING SOFTLY]

34:10.000 --> 34:11.770
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

34:11.770 --> 34:13.429
[DOOR OPENS]

34:15.020 --> 34:17.020
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

34:18.670 --> 34:20.620
MARTHA: [WHISPERS] Someone's here.

34:21.659 --> 34:23.300
Outside.

34:24.800 --> 34:26.280
[RETREATING FOOSTEPS]

34:26.280 --> 34:28.380
[DOOR OPENS]

34:31.250 --> 34:33.909
[BREATHES NERVOUSLY]

34:40.199 --> 34:42.260
OFJOSEPH: [WHISPERS] That way?

34:42.260 --> 34:43.699
Okay.

35:13.460 --> 35:15.500
- Hi.
- Hey.

35:29.450 --> 35:31.110
What?

35:35.040 --> 35:36.860
The Swiss are gonna
act as a neutral party

35:36.860 --> 35:38.310
for Nichole.

35:39.580 --> 35:41.240
[TENSE MUSIC]

35:41.240 --> 35:43.030
I made a deal with them

35:43.030 --> 35:44.680
to keep her in Canada.

35:46.670 --> 35:48.710
You made a deal with the Swiss?

35:50.880 --> 35:52.470
I need you.

35:52.470 --> 35:53.880
I need your help.
No.

35:53.880 --> 35:55.460
Yes. I...
They need information.

35:55.460 --> 35:56.500
They don't give a shit about us.

35:56.500 --> 35:58.250
Nick.

35:58.250 --> 35:59.930
Nick.

36:01.030 --> 36:03.250
- They're politicians.
OFJOSEPH: I know.

36:03.250 --> 36:04.260
They have their own agenda.

36:04.260 --> 36:06.040
So do I.

36:09.230 --> 36:10.470
You get in bed
with a government,

36:10.470 --> 36:12.120
and it's not so easy to get out.

36:20.700 --> 36:22.710
This is your one chance.

36:27.540 --> 36:29.550
This is it.

36:32.040 --> 36:33.870
This is your chance

36:33.870 --> 36:35.460
to be a father

36:35.460 --> 36:37.320
to our daughter.

36:45.880 --> 36:47.030
How many of those do you think

36:47.030 --> 36:48.690
you're gonna get?

36:53.040 --> 36:55.080
It's tomorrow morning.

37:02.570 --> 37:04.240
Okay.

37:05.270 --> 37:06.910
Okay.

37:10.980 --> 37:12.820
OFJOSEPH: Thank you.

37:15.800 --> 37:18.420
[DRAMATIC PIANO MUSIC]

37:18.420 --> 37:20.460
[DOOR OPENS, BEEPS]

37:22.790 --> 37:24.090
MATTIAS: Mr. Blaine.

37:24.090 --> 37:26.120
[DOOR CLOSES, BEEPS]

37:28.060 --> 37:30.090
This way.

37:46.050 --> 37:48.240
[DOOR OPENS]
WATERFORD: Well.

37:48.240 --> 37:50.270
Thank you so much for your time.

37:51.520 --> 37:53.920
You'll be in touch with updates?

37:53.920 --> 37:55.040
LENA: Of course.

37:55.040 --> 37:57.060
WATERFORD: Let us get your coat.

38:10.870 --> 38:12.720
What's going on?

38:13.870 --> 38:16.230
We're recommending
discussions continue.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.790
Discussions about what?

38:25.190 --> 38:26.630
Hmm?

38:28.250 --> 38:29.660
About bringing her back here?

38:29.660 --> 38:31.630
About bringing her
back to this place?

38:32.660 --> 38:34.240
LENA: Nothing has
been decided.

38:34.240 --> 38:35.600
But yes.

38:35.600 --> 38:36.960
What about Nick?

38:36.960 --> 38:38.450
LENA: We won't be
able to do business

38:38.450 --> 38:39.700
with Mr. Blaine.

38:39.700 --> 38:41.430
You made a deal!

38:41.430 --> 38:43.470
I don't think you know
who Mr. Blaine is.

38:43.470 --> 38:45.170
<i>Or</i> who he was.

38:45.170 --> 38:46.250
Our research indicates

38:46.250 --> 38:48.180
he is <i>not</i> to be trusted.

38:48.180 --> 38:49.640
No, there's been...

38:49.640 --> 38:51.710
There's some kind of mistake.

38:51.710 --> 38:53.280
I will talk to him.

38:53.280 --> 38:54.850
LENA: He's left for Chicago.

38:55.850 --> 38:58.190
Some people are not to be dealt with.

38:58.190 --> 38:59.210
WATERFORD: Now.

38:59.210 --> 39:00.240
Will we see you

39:00.240 --> 39:03.090
at this afternoon's prayers?

39:03.090 --> 39:04.300
You're more than welcome

39:04.300 --> 39:05.420
to watch the taping.

39:05.420 --> 39:06.460
LENA: Ah, no.

39:06.460 --> 39:08.260
Thank you for the invitation.

39:08.260 --> 39:09.980
But I'm sure I'll see

39:09.980 --> 39:11.700
the finished product.

39:11.700 --> 39:13.300
SERENA: Thank you.

39:23.840 --> 39:25.880
What did Nick do?

39:29.850 --> 39:31.850
Before he was a driver?

39:35.890 --> 39:37.890
He served Gilead.

39:43.870 --> 39:45.890
How did he serve Gilead?

39:47.030 --> 39:48.660
Tell me.

39:50.320 --> 39:52.560
He was a soldier in the crusade.

39:56.840 --> 39:58.860
We wouldn't be here without him.

40:10.930 --> 40:12.500
All this time you spent together

40:12.500 --> 40:14.500
and he never mentioned anything.

40:14.500 --> 40:16.740
[DARK MUSIC]

40:28.110 --> 40:30.740
[INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO]

40:32.210 --> 40:34.680
[TRAIN WHEELS RATTLING, SQUEALING]

40:42.400 --> 40:44.410
[TRAIN NOISE AMPLIFIES MENACINGLY]

40:57.060 --> 40:58.250
[AMPLIFIED TRAIN NOISE STOPS ABRUPTLY]

40:58.250 --> 41:00.260
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

41:02.660 --> 41:04.080
[DOOR OPENS]

41:04.080 --> 41:05.650
[AUNT LYDIA SIGHS]

41:05.650 --> 41:07.670
Almost time to go.

41:11.240 --> 41:13.250
Ah. Let's take a look at you.

41:21.880 --> 41:22.910
Ah!

41:25.030 --> 41:26.900
Are you all right?

41:28.860 --> 41:30.460
OFJOSEPH: I'm just tired,
Aunt Lydia.

41:30.460 --> 41:31.460
Huh.

41:31.460 --> 41:33.090
One more thing.

42:10.210 --> 42:12.350
Can I ask you...

42:12.350 --> 42:13.620
Can I ask you a question,

42:13.620 --> 42:15.250
Aunt Lydia?

42:15.250 --> 42:16.880
What is it?

42:21.890 --> 42:23.110
Do you want us all

42:23.110 --> 42:24.770
to be silenced?

42:31.030 --> 42:33.230
No.

42:33.230 --> 42:35.660
No, I don't.

42:39.410 --> 42:40.790
Ah.

42:41.810 --> 42:43.460
This trip...

42:43.460 --> 42:45.880
has been tiring, hasn't it?

42:45.880 --> 42:47.300
OFJOSEPH: Yes.

42:48.920 --> 42:50.040
AUNT LYDIA: It'll be good to...

42:50.040 --> 42:51.190
be home.

42:52.220 --> 42:53.280
OFJOSEPH: It will.

42:53.280 --> 42:54.860
[EXHALES]

42:54.860 --> 42:56.900
When I get tired...

42:59.890 --> 43:01.650
I still

43:01.650 --> 43:04.870
try to think

43:04.870 --> 43:08.260
of the good I can do

43:08.260 --> 43:10.240
in God's world.

43:11.770 --> 43:12.860
If I can help

43:12.860 --> 43:17.250
just one person,

43:17.250 --> 43:18.250
[EXHALES]

43:18.250 --> 43:21.780
one soul,

43:21.780 --> 43:23.820
that's enough.

43:33.230 --> 43:35.250
I think of you, dear.

43:44.030 --> 43:46.570
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC]

43:46.570 --> 43:49.880
[OFJOSEPH CRYING]

44:17.970 --> 44:19.610
I don't...

44:22.480 --> 44:24.500
Can you help me?

44:51.870 --> 44:53.890
[FASTENERS SNAP CLOSE]

45:12.860 --> 45:14.320
Let's go.

45:49.400 --> 45:51.410
[INDISTINCT CHATTER ON RADIO]

46:43.650 --> 46:46.030
That's nice.

46:46.030 --> 46:47.640
The silence.

46:56.670 --> 46:58.680
You could return the favor.

47:05.510 --> 47:07.830
You know, let's just stop.

47:07.830 --> 47:09.470
Please.

47:13.670 --> 47:15.040
This is all gonna be over soon.

47:15.040 --> 47:16.860
You're gonna get to go back home,

47:16.860 --> 47:18.140
and we're gonna stay here.

47:18.140 --> 47:19.460
And you and I will finally

47:19.460 --> 47:21.260
be free of one another.

47:22.660 --> 47:24.870
You will never be free of me.

47:27.390 --> 47:29.040
You will never be free of me

47:29.040 --> 47:31.470
until both of my
children are safe.

47:33.510 --> 47:36.210
That is my constant prayer
for Nichole.

47:36.210 --> 47:38.240
I trusted you.

47:39.970 --> 47:43.240
To let her have
the best life possible.

47:43.240 --> 47:44.480
To do the right thing.

47:44.480 --> 47:46.690
And I trusted you
to stay with her.

47:46.690 --> 47:47.880
I gave her the name of Nichole.

47:47.880 --> 47:49.050
I did that to honor you

47:49.050 --> 47:50.220
for getting her out.

47:50.220 --> 47:51.950
You will not let her go!

47:51.950 --> 47:53.830
Because I love her!

47:53.830 --> 47:55.870
This isn't love.

47:55.870 --> 47:57.660
You can't love!

47:57.660 --> 48:00.710
You don't know how!

48:00.710 --> 48:03.870
Serena,
you built this whole world

48:03.870 --> 48:06.900
just so that you
can have someone.

48:08.860 --> 48:10.050
But it didn't work.

48:12.670 --> 48:14.690
You're small.

48:16.540 --> 48:18.560
You're cruel.

48:20.240 --> 48:21.510
And you're empty.

48:29.550 --> 48:32.460
You will always be...

48:32.460 --> 48:34.120
empty.

48:52.940 --> 48:55.250
I should have put
a ring in your mouth

48:55.250 --> 48:57.420
the day that we met.

49:00.450 --> 49:02.050
I should have let you burn

49:02.050 --> 49:03.890
when I had the chance.

49:03.890 --> 49:05.090
[STRING MUSIC]

51:35.440 --> 51:36.890
Look at this.

51:36.890 --> 51:38.350
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

51:38.350 --> 51:39.770
Ready?

51:42.250 --> 51:44.260
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING FAINTLY]

51:49.930 --> 51:53.300
[SOMBER VOCALIZING]

52:36.400 --> 52:38.580
Lord above,

52:38.580 --> 52:40.690
we beseech you,

52:40.690 --> 52:43.320
hear our prayer.

53:00.680 --> 53:02.680
Hear...

53:02.680 --> 53:04.470
our prayer.

53:04.470 --> 53:06.110
[WATERFORD'S VOICE ECHOES]

53:30.230 --> 53:31.990
Children are a heritage

53:31.990 --> 53:33.450
from the Lord.

53:33.450 --> 53:34.510
Offspring,

53:34.510 --> 53:37.320
a reward from him.

53:37.320 --> 53:39.860
Like arrows in the hands

53:39.860 --> 53:42.200
of a warrior,

53:42.200 --> 53:45.710
are children born in one's youth.

53:45.710 --> 53:46.720
Blessed

53:46.720 --> 53:48.660
is the man whose quiver

53:48.660 --> 53:50.510
is full of them.

53:50.510 --> 53:54.240
They will not be put to shame

53:54.240 --> 53:57.440
when they contend
with their enemies.

53:57.440 --> 53:59.090
Hear our prayer.

54:22.820 --> 54:24.820
[QUIET, AMBIENT NOISE]

